###########################################################################################
# PARAMETERS' DEFINITION FOR THE FARHADGERD NETWORK
# Source: Table A1, A2, A3 (Farhadgerd water distribution network)
# 53 demand/junction nodes + 1 reservoir (node 0 = R-1)
# Node mapping: R-1=0, J-1=1, J-2=2, ..., J-53=53
# Demands converted from L/s to m^3/s (divided by 1000)
# Hazen-Williams C: 120 or 130 per pipe (see comments in arcs)
# Minimum pressure = 15 m above ground level at all demand nodes
# All pipe diameters are decision variables (no fixed existing pipes)
# Candidate diameters from Table A1

# paper link:  https://cdnsciencepub.com/doi/10.1139/cjce-2018-0137

###########################################################################################

